profile_positions.description:
+ Define and execute projects related to capacity expansion and process stability and performance;
+ Support process development and roadmap activities needed for future InP technology;
+ Review product requirements with the manufacturing staff to ensure compatibility of processing methods;
+ Compile and evaluate test data to determine appropriate limits and variation for process or material specifications.

+ Development of thin-film technology for medical devices: process design and optimization, fabrication of thin-film based devices, testing;
+ Development of processes, process maturing and yield optimising for manufacturing;
+ Review of work instructions and standards for process documentation;
+ Manage and lead a small team in cleanroom for R&D and manufacturing activities;
+ Define and execute development activities and projects for capacity expansion and up-scaling;
+ Manage the relation with different stakeholders and be the first contact with external collaborators;
+ Participate in different cross functional teams, interface between manufacturing operations and leadership team.
